11:31.535 --> 11:33.435
Get up! Get up there! Get up there!

11:43.948 --> 11:45.347
What's that in the back?

11:45.383 --> 11:46.913
- It's a man.
- Is he dead?

11:46.916 --> 11:47.916
Get away from there.

11:47.952 --> 11:50.386
- Did you run him over?
- Get. Go on, get.

11:50.421 --> 11:52.287
Oh, my God.

11:52.323 --> 11:54.089
Go inside.

11:54.125 --> 11:55.758
Jeannie, are you okay?

11:55.793 --> 11:58.360
Everybody's fine.

11:58.396 --> 12:00.429
All right, go on with your granddaddy.

12:00.464 --> 12:02.464
You too. Get on in there.

12:06.070 --> 12:07.903
Somebody strung up one
of Pedro García's hands

12:07.938 --> 12:09.405
by the side of the road.

12:09.440 --> 12:11.640
I wasn't gonna leave him there.

12:13.944 --> 12:16.311
Should we cancel this party?

12:17.314 --> 12:18.580
We can't.

12:18.616 --> 12:19.982
We got to show the world

12:20.017 --> 12:22.918
South Texas is a great
place to do business.

12:25.656 --> 12:27.523
I'm sorry, baby.

12:29.326 --> 12:31.093
I understand.

12:51.148 --> 12:52.614
Here's your julep.

12:52.650 --> 12:54.983
Ah, 'tis that time.

12:58.001 --> 12:59.367
Oh, yeah.

12:59.401 --> 13:01.623
That's spot-on-the-nose
perfect, darlin'.

13:01.659 --> 13:04.426
But just for the sake of an experiment,

13:04.462 --> 13:06.829
would you mind passing
me that bottle over there?

13:13.804 --> 13:15.471
Ohh, yeah.

13:16.807 --> 13:18.140
You're gonna be drunk.

13:18.175 --> 13:20.609
Oh, honey if you had to lay down

13:20.644 --> 13:23.479
as much bullshit as I'm
about to lay down tonight,

13:23.514 --> 13:24.746
you'd get drunk, too.

13:24.782 --> 13:26.348
Here you go.

13:26.383 --> 13:28.317
Come here. Hey.

13:29.720 --> 13:31.987
You see that rig out there?

13:32.022 --> 13:33.088
Yeah.

13:33.123 --> 13:34.756
After I get done tonight,

13:34.792 --> 13:38.627
we'll have enough money to
buy six more just like it.

13:38.662 --> 13:40.329
Why do we need so many?

13:40.364 --> 13:43.632
We're running out of time.

13:43.667 --> 13:47.236
Another year like the one we
just endured will finish us.

13:50.307 --> 13:54.209
The era of the cattle
baron is over, honey.

13:54.245 --> 13:56.645
It's over.

13:56.680 --> 14:00.716
What if there isn't
any oil in the ground?

14:00.751 --> 14:03.519
Oh, I'm betting there is.

14:03.554 --> 14:05.854
But what if you're wrong?

14:05.890 --> 14:08.724
If there's no oil, do we lose the ranch?

14:08.759 --> 14:11.360
Well, that's always a risk.

14:11.395 --> 14:14.496
Any time you find a
decent piece of land,

14:14.532 --> 14:16.832
sure as sunup,

14:16.867 --> 14:19.701
someone out there's gonna
try and take it from you.

14:21.171 --> 14:23.105
Does that scare you?

14:25.738 --> 14:27.609
Not anymore.

15:33.944 --> 15:37.379
Oh. Nice to see you back, Miss García.

15:37.414 --> 15:39.247
That's my father's man.

15:39.283 --> 15:42.050
Yeah. Damn shame.

15:42.086 --> 15:43.819
Poor old Armando.

15:45.656 --> 15:47.289
They say he was, uh, riding

15:47.324 --> 15:50.025
with the Mexican bandits, though.

15:53.764 --> 15:55.063
Who found him?

15:55.099 --> 15:57.132
Pete McCullough.

16:07.645 --> 16:08.777
Well.

16:08.812 --> 16:11.813
If it ain't Pete McCullough.

16:14.785 --> 16:18.520
You getting ready for that
fête galant-ay tonight?

16:18.555 --> 16:21.623
I had my shirt pressed special.

16:21.659 --> 16:23.258
You have a hand in that?

16:23.293 --> 16:25.994
I'm sure I don't know
what you're talking about.

16:26.030 --> 16:27.295
Niles.

16:31.535 --> 16:33.135
Well...

16:35.539 --> 16:39.207
If you're referring to that
strung-up cattle rustler,

16:39.243 --> 16:41.209
now that you menti it,

16:41.245 --> 16:43.211
I might know something about that.

16:43.247 --> 16:46.381
Armando couldn't rustle up
supper, let alone 70 head.

16:47.685 --> 16:51.186
He was confederating
with the sediciosos, Pete.

16:51.221 --> 16:54.690
Armando cut the fence,
and he looked the other way

16:54.725 --> 16:58.360
when them Mexers stole your property.

16:58.395 --> 17:02.898
I tell you, my friend,
he admitted to all of it.

17:04.268 --> 17:05.901
In the end.

17:05.935 --> 17:07.969
Jesus, Niles.

17:10.107 --> 17:14.009
You and your daddy
ain't exactly strangers

17:14.044 --> 17:16.545
to backcountry adjudication.

17:16.579 --> 17:20.882
You enlightened plenty of
rustlers at the end of a rope.

17:20.917 --> 17:23.518
That ain't how we do things anymore.

17:23.554 --> 17:25.554
Oh.

17:25.589 --> 17:27.888
If I catch someone stealing my property,

17:27.925 --> 17:30.859
I'll see that he's dealt with.

17:30.894 --> 17:33.729
I don't want your help.

17:33.764 --> 17:35.230
You hear me?

17:35.265 --> 17:38.567
Oh, I hear you all right.

17:38.602 --> 17:42.571
But you might want to make sure
your daddy is of a similar mind.

17:54.284 --> 17:56.852
I had a little talk with Niles Gilbert.

17:56.887 --> 17:57.853
That so?

17:57.888 --> 17:59.287
Yep.

18:02.326 --> 18:04.926
Is this one of them vaudeville routines,

18:04.962 --> 18:07.229
or are you working your
way up to a question?

18:08.232 --> 18:10.899
Did you put him up to hanging that man?

18:12.169 --> 18:14.102
I asked him to sniff around about,

18:14.138 --> 18:15.737
see who was hitting our cattle.

18:15.773 --> 18:18.607
And you didn't consider
how he might interpret that?

18:21.745 --> 18:24.579
I don't want this family in bed
with the Law and Order League.

18:24.615 --> 18:27.382
And I don't want the home I
spent my whole life building

18:27.417 --> 18:30.852
to get snatched out from
underneath our noses.

18:41.698 --> 18:42.964
Sometimes it feels like

18:43.000 --> 18:44.800
I'm in the front of
the boat bailing water

18:44.835 --> 18:48.270
while you're behind me drilling holes.

18:48.305 --> 18:52.407
Who's running this
ranch, Daddy... you or me?

18:52.442 --> 18:53.608
Well...

18:55.379 --> 18:59.481
